# Supabase — copy to `.env.local` and replace ALL placeholder values with your project’s
# real URL + anon key (Project Settings → API). Never commit `.env.local`.
#
# --- Vercel (required for deployed site; never commit real keys to git) ---
# 1) Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# 2) Add NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY with REAL values
#    from Supabase → Project Settings → API (not the placeholder lines below).
# 3) Enable for Production AND Preview (checkboxes for each variable).
# 4) Deployments → … → Redeploy — turn OFF “Use existing Build Cache” once so the
#    client bundle is rebuilt with the new NEXT_PUBLIC_* values.
#
# Placeholders only — replace in .env.local on your machine; on Vercel use the dashboard.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-or-publishable-key-here

# Optional: server-only — never expose to the browser.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_secret_service_role_key

# Oral practice (`/practice` hub, `/practice/session` evaluator): override `question_sets.slug` (default: mvp-orals-v1).
# ORAL_QUESTION_SET_SLUG=my-custom-set-slug

# If questions are still `draft` in Supabase, set to 1 so practice can load them.
# ORAL_INCLUDE_DRAFT_QUESTIONS=1

# Optional: restrict `/practice` to one question slug (e.g. lost-comms-vfr). Omit or use * for full set.
# ORAL_PRACTICE_ONLY_SLUG=lost-comms-vfr
